      "text": "Tongue of the Fatman (or simply Fatman for the Japan release) is a 1989 fighting game developed by Brian A. Rice, Inc. and published by Activision.\nThe game is also renamed by the titles Mondu's Fight Palace on the Commodore 64, and Slaughter Sport in its Sega Genesis iteration. The working title for the game was 'Red Belt'.",
